Key Match Events: France opened the scoring with a goal by Randal Kolo Muani after a cross by Kylian Mbappe.
Jonathan Clauss scored a stunning goal from outside the box to give France a two-goal lead.
Kylian Mbappe scored the final goal for France after being set up by Bradley Barcola.
Post-Match Reflections: Didier Deschamps expressed concern about France's lack of efficiency in converting chances.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match served as a warm-up for Euro 2024.
The game was played at Stade Saint-Symphorien.
